claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: A table summarizing influenza vaccine efficacy in adults 18–49 years of age (Study 1), comparing Flublok (N=2344) to saline placebo (N=2304) across various case definitions (positive culture with strain matched to vaccine, any influenza-like illness, positive culture with any strain, etc.), showing number of cases, rates (%), vaccine efficacy (%) and 95% confidence intervals. The image presents clinical efficacy data for Flublok versus placebo but provides no information on how Flublok is produced, so it does not support the claim about a novel BEVS platform in insect cells. Note: The table is clear and fully legible; however, it contains only efficacy outcomes and no manufacturing or production platform details.
